Roles &amp; Responsibilities:
Assist in the administration of bankruptcy estates, including but not limited to providing administrative support, attending meetings, and perform tasks necessary to ensure compliance with statutory requirements.  Responsibilities include (list not exhaustive):
• Prepare and send out emails,  letters and reports to the Official Assignee as specified.                                     
• Maintain database of records and ensure that proper follow-up actions are taken.                                      
•  Ensuring payments made by bankrupts are properly recorded.  Follow-up actions are taken for payments that are in arrears.                                                                                                                                         
•  Ensuring that all statutory and other documents as specified are submitted properly.

Requirements:
·  Minimum Diploma in Accountancy or other relevant qualifications